data.text:
The Memoirs of Sherlock Holmes: The Dying Detective

Holmes and Watson attempt to solve a mystery involving the highly intelligent and manipulative doctor, Culverton Smith, who specialises in tropical medicine. When the doctor's wealthy cousin dies of a rare tropical disease and leaves Culverton all his money and property despite having a wife and children, Holmes and Watson become determined to set things right.
